{
  "text": "In recognition-recall CaRP, a password is a sequence of some invariant points of objects. An invariant point of an object (e.g. letter -A\u2016) is a point that has a fixed relative position in different incarnations (e.g., fonts) of the object, and thus can be uniquely identified by humans no matter how the object appears in CaRP images. It contains two schemes [CITATION_1] A. TextPoints B. TextPoints4CR",
  "citation_candidates": [
